  <original-body>The git support for `Generator::Commands::Create#file` uses `relative_destination`.  But when doing the initial app generation, the working directory is the *parent* of the app directory, and from there `relative_destination` is broken.  This results in a pile of error messages like

@@@
$ rails fooproj --git
      create  Rakefile
fatal: pathspec 'Rakefile' did not match any files
...
      create  log/test.log
fatal: pathspec 'log/test.log' did not match any files
@@@

...not that you really want log/test.log tracked by your VCS, but that's another story.</original-body>
